history.content: Your best bet would be to contact the CS70 staff for next sem. Reader appointments are often not prioritized and therefore, do not come out until early in the new year for the Spring semester.

The student response is correct, contacting the instructor or Head TA might help.


However, it's not that Reader appointments aren't prioritized. They are intentionally hired after uGSIs so that students do not accept a Reader position and then abandon it for the uGSI position. 

Our hiring timeline has moved up and Reader hiring should be mostly complete before 12/22

This is my first time doing the application for reader. I haven’t received offer for any position I choosed for my application, which was several days after the priority deadline I believe.

Does this mean that I have no chance to have any position for next semester? I chose CS70’s reader as my high intended position, is it possible that some more position for readers come out at the beginning of the next semester? ( Someone reject the offer/ class is expanded)
